<br>
Here are the basics though:<br>
<br>
Earth:  highest hp's...highest hand to hand damage.<br>
Air.   :  Average hand to hand damage..but they stun opponent<br>
Ice:     Only pet with a distance DD and it is very good...not so good in combat though.<br>
<br>
The strength is COMBINING the pets though...depending on the mob...if they are a caster..lead with air then ice, ice...the air keeps them stunned and the ice or earth just rip them up..you do lose xp though for using pets...I believe the last patch limit put the max at 25%.<br>
<br>
Currently I can solo yellows with ease and oranges with 1/3 mana remaining...very powerful class...<br>
<br>
To me though..the key is choosing the right mixture of pet to mob and keeping the numbers of them to a minimum...also, air spec has the most damaging DD with the least mana usage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/bdaggersincamelot.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=belce>Belce</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.macaulay.org/macabdge.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(10/30/01 3:40:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.macaulay.org/macabdge.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gam a Question</span><hr size=1> Soloin yellows is something I have found to be easy now too, I am considering trying an orange as well just to see if it is possible.  Right now a yellow will take me down to about, just over 3/4 health and bit under that in stamina left.<br>
